^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|An important signaling technique by klaus at trick three. In general, to encourage, you play your 2nd highest in a suit if you can afford it. In this hand, that would mean on the Q of spades, klaus would play the 10. However, klaus can't really afford the 10, so he plays the highest one he can afford which is the 8. In general, when encouraging, throw the highest card you can.  I notice people often play their 2nd lowest when they have 4. So, if they have, say A864 and want to encourage, they play the six. It is  much better to play the eight. Hit partner over the head if you can, lol.|
