AT|

One thing to remember is, once you bid 4N, you are responsible for placing the final contract. Your partner just answers your questions, and should not override your decision. Therefore, you need to know what you are going to bid over any response, before you bid Blackwood. Basically, you should bid slam if you are not missing any Key cards, or if you are missing one Key card and not the Q of trumps. Your decision making as the Blackwood bidder is very straight forward.|
